<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/StatusAssertion/1336> rdfs:label "Status Assertion: #1336" ;
	a dprr:StatusAssertion ;
	dprr:isDateStartUncertain true ;
	dprr:isAboutPerson <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/Person/2634> ;
	dprr:hasStatus <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/Status/2> ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySource <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/21> ;
	dprr:hasDateStart -47 ;
	dprr:hasDateEnd -43 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7865> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7865" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Praetor 45? His praetorship, inferred from his command in Bithynia and Pontus in 44-43, remains uncertain (Sumner, Phoenix 25, 1971, 361).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6199> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6199" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Commander of a legion and of a squadron of Cassius' fleet, he outflanked Decidius and Norbanus in the pass of the Corpilans (App. Be 4.102) and later joined his commander at Philippi (4.105, no title preserved)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6081> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6081" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Governor, probably Proconsul, in Bithynia and Pontus (see 44, Promagistrates). He sent a fleet against Dolabella (see Quaestors, on Turullius; Cic. Fam. 12.13.3), and himself led an army against him in Asia Minor (Cic. Ad Brut. 1.6.3; Dio 47.31.1-2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6008> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6008" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Governor, probably Proconsul, of Bithynia and Pontus, appointed before Caesar's death (App. BC 3.2; cf. Plut. Brut. 19.2). An active member of the conspiracy, he initiated proceedings on the Ides of March by asking for pardon for his brother (Nic. Dam. Vit. Caes. 24, FGrH 2A.408f.; Suet. Iul. 82.1; Plut. Caes. 66.3-4; Brut. 17.2-4; App. BC 2.113, and 117; Dio 47.31.1; cf. Cic. Phil. 2.27; Senec. Ep. Mor. 83.12; Ira 3.30.4-5; Dio 44.19.4). He immediately departed to Bithynia, succeeding Marcius Crispus, and prepared a fleet (Cic. Fam. 12.13.3) as well as money and troops at Brutus' request (App. BC 3.6; see 43, Promagistrates). See Sternkopf, Hermes 47 (1912) 331." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5882> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5882" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably Praetor in 45, since he became Proconsul of Bithynia and Pontus in 44 (see 44, Promagistrates)." .
